{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01JYshoMJhqr1KG8m8TBHjLs","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01UWVVzdzc77xZKiKvHCX5Ld","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Execute full Quarkus to Spring migration","prompt":"You are migrating a DayTrader application from Quarkus to Spring Boot 3.x. The working directory is:\n/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_2/output\n\nI need you to write ALL the following files. Use the Write tool for new files and the Edit tool for modifications.\n\n## 1. NEW FILE: pom.xml - Spring Boot 3.x pom (REPLACE existing)\n\nWrite a Spring Boot 3.2.x pom.xml with:\n- parent: spring-boot-starter-parent 3.2.5\n- groupId: io.openliberty.samples, artifactId: daytrader-spring\n- Java 17\n- Dependencies: spring-boot-starter-web, spring-boot-starter-data-jpa, spring-boot-starter-validation, h2 (runtime), jackson-databind, spring-boot-starter-test (test scope)\n- spring-boot-maven-plugin in build\n- No Quarkus dependencies at all\n\n## 2. NEW FILE: src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/DayTraderApplication.java\n\nSpring Boot main class with @SpringBootApplication and @EnableScheduling\n\n## 3. EDIT: src/main/resources/application.properties\n\nReplace with Spring Boot properties:\n```\nserver.port=8080\nserver.servlet.context-path=/\nspring.datasource.url=jdbc:h2:mem:tradedb;DB_CLOSE_DELAY=-1\nspring.datasource.driverClassName=org.h2.Driver\nspring.datasource.username=sa\nspring.datasource.password=\nspring.jpa.database-platform=org.hibernate.dialect.H2Dialect\nspring.jpa.hibernate.ddl-auto=create-drop\nspring.jpa.show-sql=false\nspring.jpa.open-in-view=true\nspring.h2.console.enabled=true\ntrade.runtime-mode=EJB3\ntrade.order-processing-mode=SYNCH\ntrade.max-users=50\ntrade.max-quotes=100\ntrade.db.populate.on.startup=true\nspring.jackson.serialization.fail-on-empty-beans=false\n```\n\n## 4. EDIT: Migrate ALL JAX-RS REST resources to Spring MVC controllers\n\n### TradeResource.java - Convert to Spring @RestController:\n- Replace jakarta.ws.rs imports with Spring imports (RestController, GetMapping, PostMapping, RequestParam, PathVariable, ResponseEntity)\n- Replace @Path with @RequestMapping(\"/rest/trade\")\n- Replace @GET @Path(\"/market\") with @GetMapping(\"/market\")\n- Replace @POST @Path(\"/login\") with @PostMapping(\"/login\")\n- Replace @Inject with @Autowired (or constructor injection)\n- Replace Response.ok() with ResponseEntity.ok()\n- Replace @FormParam with @RequestParam\n- Replace @PathParam with @PathVariable\n\n### QuoteResource.java - Convert similarly:\n- @RestController @RequestMapping(\"/rest/quotes\")\n\n### MessagingResource.java - Convert similarly:\n- @RestController @RequestMapping(\"/rest/messaging\")\n\n### TradeAppResource.java - Convert similarly:\n- @RestController @RequestMapping(\"/rest/app\")\n- Change all form endpoints similarly\n\n## 5. EDIT: Migrate CDI beans to Spring beans\n\n### TradeSLSBBean.java:\n- Replace @ApplicationScoped with @Service\n- Replace @Inject with @Autowired\n- Replace @Transactional (jakarta.transaction) with @Transactional (org.springframework.transaction.annotation)\n- Replace EntityManager @Inject with @PersistenceContext\n- Remove all CDI qualifier annotations (@Default, @TradeEJB, @RuntimeMode, @Trace)\n- Remove jakarta.enterprise imports, add Spring imports\n- Make it implement TradeServices and be the primary service with @Primary annotation\n- Replace jakarta.transaction.RollbackException with appropriate Spring exception\n\n### MarketSummarySingleton.java:\n- Replace @ApplicationScoped with @Service\n- Replace @Inject with @Autowired/@PersistenceContext\n- Replace @Scheduled(every = \"20s\") with @Scheduled(fixedRate = 20000)\n- Remove CDI Event, use Spring ApplicationEventPublisher instead (or just remove the event)\n- Remove io.quarkus.scheduler import, use org.springframework.scheduling.annotation.Scheduled\n\n### DirectSLSBBean.java:\n- Replace @ApplicationScoped with @Service(\"directSLSBBean\")\n- Remove CDI qualifier annotations\n- Replace @Inject with @Autowired @Qualifier\n\n### TradeDirect.java:\n- Replace @Dependent with @Service(\"tradeDirect\") @Scope(\"prototype\")\n- Replace @Inject DataSource with @Autowired DataSource\n- Replace @Inject UserTransaction with Spring's PlatformTransactionManager (or just use DataSource transactions directly since TradeDirect manages its own JDBC connections)\n- Remove UserTransaction usage - TradeDirect already manages commits/rollbacks via JDBC connection. Replace txn.begin()/commit()/rollback() with connection-level transaction management\n- Replace io.quarkus.narayana.jta.QuarkusTransaction with nothing (remove)\n- Replace CDI Event with ApplicationEventPublisher or remove\n- Remove @MarketSummaryUpdate, @RuntimeMode, @Trace, @TradeJDBC annotations\n- Replace @Inject MessageProducerService with @Autowired\n\n### AsyncOrderSubmitter.java:\n- Replace @RequestScoped with @Service\n- Replace io.quarkus.virtual.threads.VirtualThreads ExecutorService with a simple @Autowired TaskExecutor or just use Executors.newCachedThreadPool()\n- Remove @VirtualThreads\n\n### AsyncOrder.java:\n- Replace @Dependent with @Component @Scope(\"prototype\")\n- Replace @Inject @TradeJDBC with @Autowired @Qualifier(\"tradeDirect\")\n- Replace jakarta.transaction.Transactional with Spring @Transactional\n\n### AsyncScheduledOrderSubmitter.java:\n- Replace @RequestScoped with @Service \n- Remove @VirtualThreads, use Spring @Async or simple executor\n\n### AsyncScheduledOrder.java:\n- Replace @Dependent with @Component @Scope(\"prototype\")\n- Replace CDI Instance<TradeServices> with @Autowired TradeServices (use @Primary)\n\n### DatabasePopulator.java:\n- Replace @ApplicationScoped with @Component\n- Replace @Inject EntityManager with @PersistenceContext EntityManager\n- Replace @ConfigProperty with @Value\n- Replace io.quarkus.runtime.StartupEvent with @PostConstruct or implement CommandLineRunner\n- Replace void onStart(@Observes StartupEvent ev) with @PostConstruct void init() or @EventListener(ApplicationReadyEvent.class)\n\n### TradeDirectDBUtils.java:\n- Replace @ApplicationScoped with @Service\n- Replace @Inject AgroalDataSource with @Autowired DataSource\n- Replace io.agroal.api.AgroalDataSource with javax.sql.DataSource\n- Replace @Inject @TradeJDBC TradeServices with @Autowired @Qualifier(\"tradeDirect\") TradeServices\n\n### MessageProducerService.java:\n- Replace SmallRye Reactive Messaging with Spring's ApplicationEventPublisher\n- Replace @Inject @Channel Emitter with ApplicationEventPublisher\n- Remove all SmallRye/MicroProfile imports\n- Use applicationEventPublisher.publishEvent() instead of emitter.send()\n- Create simple wrapper event classes or use the POJO directly\n\n### DTBroker3MDB.java:\n- Replace @Incoming with Spring @EventListener\n- Replace @ApplicationScoped with @Service\n- Remove MicroProfile imports\n- Method signature: @EventListener public void onMessage(OrderMessage message)\n\n### DTStreamer3MDB.java:\n- Replace @Incoming with Spring @EventListener\n- Replace @ApplicationScoped with @Service\n- Remove MicroProfile imports\n\n### RecentQuotePriceChangeList.java:\n- Replace @ApplicationScoped with @Service\n- Replace CDI Event with Spring ApplicationEventPublisher\n- Remove CDI @Inject @QuotePriceChange Event\n\n## 6. EDIT: Interface annotations\n\n### Remove CDI qualifiers from interfaces:\n- RuntimeMode.java: Remove @Qualifier import and annotation, keep as plain annotation\n- TradeEJB.java: Remove @Qualifier, keep as plain annotation  \n- TradeJDBC.java: Remove @Qualifier, keep as plain annotation\n- TradeSession2Direct.java: Remove @Qualifier, keep as plain annotation\n- Trace.java: Remove @InterceptorBinding, keep as plain annotation\n- QuotePriceChange.java: Remove @Qualifier, keep as plain annotation\n- MarketSummaryUpdate.java: Remove @Qualifier, keep as plain annotation\n\n### TradeRunTimeModeLiteral.java:\n- Remove AnnotationLiteral usage (not needed in Spring)\n- Simplify to a plain utility class or remove if not needed\n\n## 7. EDIT: Dockerfile\n\nReplace with:\n```\nFROM maven:3.9.12-ibm-semeru-21-noble\n\nUSER root\nRUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends curl lsof python3-venv python3-full \\\n    && curl -LsSf https://astral.sh/uv/install.sh | sh\n\nENV PATH=\"/root/.local/bin:$PATH\"\nENV PLAYWRIGHT_BROWSERS_PATH=/ms-playwright\nRUN mkdir -p /ms-playwright && chmod 755 /ms-playwright\n\nRUN uv venv /opt/venv \\\n    && uv pip install --python /opt/venv/bin/python playwright==1.47.0 pytest\n\nENV PATH=\"/opt/venv/bin:$PATH\"\nRUN playwright install --with-deps chromium\n\nWORKDIR /app\nCOPY . .\nRUN if [ -f mvnw ]; then chmod +x mvnw; fi && if [ -f smoke.py ]; then chmod +x smoke.py; fi\nRUN mvn clean package -DskipTests\nCMD [\"java\", \"-jar\", \"target/daytrader-spring-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar\"]\n```\n\n## 8. NEW FILE: smoke.py\n\nCreate a smoke test file that tests:\n- GET /rest/trade/market (200)\n- GET /rest/quotes/s:0 (200, returns quote data)\n- POST /rest/trade/login with uid:0/xxx (200)\n- GET /rest/trade/account/uid:0 (200)\n- GET /rest/trade/account/uid:0/holdings (200)\n- POST /rest/trade/buy (200)\n- POST /rest/messaging/ping/broker (200)\n- POST /rest/messaging/ping/streamer (200)\n- GET /rest/messaging/stats (200)\n- GET /rest/app (200, welcome page)\n\nThe smoke.py should accept BASE_URL as environment variable (default http://localhost:8080), use requests library, and print PASS/FAIL for each test.\n\n## 9. DELETE old Quarkus test files\n\nThe Quarkus test files use @QuarkusTest and RestAssured which won't work with Spring Boot. Remove them:\n- src/test/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/TradeResourceTest.java\n- src/test/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/messaging/MessagingTest.java\n- src/test/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/messaging/MessagingResourceTest.java\n\n## IMPORTANT NOTES:\n- Entity classes (AccountDataBean, OrderDataBean, QuoteDataBean, HoldingDataBean, AccountProfileDataBean) should remain UNCHANGED - they use standard JPA annotations that work with both Quarkus and Spring\n- Bean classes (RunStatsDataBean, MarketSummaryDataBean) should remain UNCHANGED\n- Messaging POJOs (OrderMessage, QuoteUpdateMessage) should remain UNCHANGED\n- Utility classes (TradeConfig, Log, MDBStats, TimerStat, FinancialUtils, KeyBlock, KeySequenceDirect) should remain UNCHANGED\n- TradeServices interface should remain UNCHANGED\n- TradeDB interface should remain UNCHANGED\n\nFor the TradeDirect class, the key challenge is UserTransaction. Since TradeDirect manages its own JDBC connections with manual commit/rollback, the simplest approach is:\n- For the 2-phase transaction (ASYNCH_2PHASE mode), simply fall back to using connection-level transactions\n- Remove UserTransaction entirely since TradeDirect already handles connection commits\n- Set inGlobalTxn to false in the places where txn.begin() was called\n- Remove the QuarkusTransaction import\n\nFor the MessageProducerService migration to Spring events:\n- Use ApplicationEventPublisher\n- The DTBroker3MDB and DTStreamer3MDB will use @EventListener to receive events\n\nNow execute ALL these changes. Write every file completely.","subagent_type":"general-purpose"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":9865,"cache_creation_input_tokens":29826,"cache_read_input_tokens":106014,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":29826,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":3262},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0a2ab8cf-d9b3-4fb3-875c-ac24a464972f","uuid":"38e8a431-3828-429c-b506-0f6f017292ba"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"You are migrating a DayTrader application from Quarkus to Spring Boot 3.x. The working directory is:\n/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__quarkus__spring/run_2/output\n\nI need you to write ALL the following files. Use the Write tool for new files and the Edit tool for modifications.\n\n## 1. NEW FILE: pom.xml - Spring Boot 3.x pom (REPLACE existing)\n\nWrite a Spring Boot 3.2.x pom.xml with:\n- parent: spring-boot-starter-parent 3.2.5\n- groupId: io.openliberty.samples, artifactId: daytrader-spring\n- Java 17\n- Dependencies: spring-boot-starter-web, spring-boot-starter-data-jpa, spring-boot-starter-validation, h2 (runtime), jackson-databind, spring-boot-starter-test (test scope)\n- spring-boot-maven-plugin in build\n- No Quarkus dependencies at all\n\n## 2. NEW FILE: src/main/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/DayTraderApplication.java\n\nSpring Boot main class with @SpringBootApplication and @EnableScheduling\n\n## 3. EDIT: src/main/resources/application.properties\n\nReplace with Spring Boot properties:\n```\nserver.port=8080\nserver.servlet.context-path=/\nspring.datasource.url=jdbc:h2:mem:tradedb;DB_CLOSE_DELAY=-1\nspring.datasource.driverClassName=org.h2.Driver\nspring.datasource.username=sa\nspring.datasource.password=\nspring.jpa.database-platform=org.hibernate.dialect.H2Dialect\nspring.jpa.hibernate.ddl-auto=create-drop\nspring.jpa.show-sql=false\nspring.jpa.open-in-view=true\nspring.h2.console.enabled=true\ntrade.runtime-mode=EJB3\ntrade.order-processing-mode=SYNCH\ntrade.max-users=50\ntrade.max-quotes=100\ntrade.db.populate.on.startup=true\nspring.jackson.serialization.fail-on-empty-beans=false\n```\n\n## 4. EDIT: Migrate ALL JAX-RS REST resources to Spring MVC controllers\n\n### TradeResource.java - Convert to Spring @RestController:\n- Replace jakarta.ws.rs imports with Spring imports (RestController, GetMapping, PostMapping, RequestParam, PathVariable, ResponseEntity)\n- Replace @Path with @RequestMapping(\"/rest/trade\")\n- Replace @GET @Path(\"/market\") with @GetMapping(\"/market\")\n- Replace @POST @Path(\"/login\") with @PostMapping(\"/login\")\n- Replace @Inject with @Autowired (or constructor injection)\n- Replace Response.ok() with ResponseEntity.ok()\n- Replace @FormParam with @RequestParam\n- Replace @PathParam with @PathVariable\n\n### QuoteResource.java - Convert similarly:\n- @RestController @RequestMapping(\"/rest/quotes\")\n\n### MessagingResource.java - Convert similarly:\n- @RestController @RequestMapping(\"/rest/messaging\")\n\n### TradeAppResource.java - Convert similarly:\n- @RestController @RequestMapping(\"/rest/app\")\n- Change all form endpoints similarly\n\n## 5. EDIT: Migrate CDI beans to Spring beans\n\n### TradeSLSBBean.java:\n- Replace @ApplicationScoped with @Service\n- Replace @Inject with @Autowired\n- Replace @Transactional (jakarta.transaction) with @Transactional (org.springframework.transaction.annotation)\n- Replace EntityManager @Inject with @PersistenceContext\n- Remove all CDI qualifier annotations (@Default, @TradeEJB, @RuntimeMode, @Trace)\n- Remove jakarta.enterprise imports, add Spring imports\n- Make it implement TradeServices and be the primary service with @Primary annotation\n- Replace jakarta.transaction.RollbackException with appropriate Spring exception\n\n### MarketSummarySingleton.java:\n- Replace @ApplicationScoped with @Service\n- Replace @Inject with @Autowired/@PersistenceContext\n- Replace @Scheduled(every = \"20s\") with @Scheduled(fixedRate = 20000)\n- Remove CDI Event, use Spring ApplicationEventPublisher instead (or just remove the event)\n- Remove io.quarkus.scheduler import, use org.springframework.scheduling.annotation.Scheduled\n\n### DirectSLSBBean.java:\n- Replace @ApplicationScoped with @Service(\"directSLSBBean\")\n- Remove CDI qualifier annotations\n- Replace @Inject with @Autowired @Qualifier\n\n### TradeDirect.java:\n- Replace @Dependent with @Service(\"tradeDirect\") @Scope(\"prototype\")\n- Replace @Inject DataSource with @Autowired DataSource\n- Replace @Inject UserTransaction with Spring's PlatformTransactionManager (or just use DataSource transactions directly since TradeDirect manages its own JDBC connections)\n- Remove UserTransaction usage - TradeDirect already manages commits/rollbacks via JDBC connection. Replace txn.begin()/commit()/rollback() with connection-level transaction management\n- Replace io.quarkus.narayana.jta.QuarkusTransaction with nothing (remove)\n- Replace CDI Event with ApplicationEventPublisher or remove\n- Remove @MarketSummaryUpdate, @RuntimeMode, @Trace, @TradeJDBC annotations\n- Replace @Inject MessageProducerService with @Autowired\n\n### AsyncOrderSubmitter.java:\n- Replace @RequestScoped with @Service\n- Replace io.quarkus.virtual.threads.VirtualThreads ExecutorService with a simple @Autowired TaskExecutor or just use Executors.newCachedThreadPool()\n- Remove @VirtualThreads\n\n### AsyncOrder.java:\n- Replace @Dependent with @Component @Scope(\"prototype\")\n- Replace @Inject @TradeJDBC with @Autowired @Qualifier(\"tradeDirect\")\n- Replace jakarta.transaction.Transactional with Spring @Transactional\n\n### AsyncScheduledOrderSubmitter.java:\n- Replace @RequestScoped with @Service \n- Remove @VirtualThreads, use Spring @Async or simple executor\n\n### AsyncScheduledOrder.java:\n- Replace @Dependent with @Component @Scope(\"prototype\")\n- Replace CDI Instance<TradeServices> with @Autowired TradeServices (use @Primary)\n\n### DatabasePopulator.java:\n- Replace @ApplicationScoped with @Component\n- Replace @Inject EntityManager with @PersistenceContext EntityManager\n- Replace @ConfigProperty with @Value\n- Replace io.quarkus.runtime.StartupEvent with @PostConstruct or implement CommandLineRunner\n- Replace void onStart(@Observes StartupEvent ev) with @PostConstruct void init() or @EventListener(ApplicationReadyEvent.class)\n\n### TradeDirectDBUtils.java:\n- Replace @ApplicationScoped with @Service\n- Replace @Inject AgroalDataSource with @Autowired DataSource\n- Replace io.agroal.api.AgroalDataSource with javax.sql.DataSource\n- Replace @Inject @TradeJDBC TradeServices with @Autowired @Qualifier(\"tradeDirect\") TradeServices\n\n### MessageProducerService.java:\n- Replace SmallRye Reactive Messaging with Spring's ApplicationEventPublisher\n- Replace @Inject @Channel Emitter with ApplicationEventPublisher\n- Remove all SmallRye/MicroProfile imports\n- Use applicationEventPublisher.publishEvent() instead of emitter.send()\n- Create simple wrapper event classes or use the POJO directly\n\n### DTBroker3MDB.java:\n- Replace @Incoming with Spring @EventListener\n- Replace @ApplicationScoped with @Service\n- Remove MicroProfile imports\n- Method signature: @EventListener public void onMessage(OrderMessage message)\n\n### DTStreamer3MDB.java:\n- Replace @Incoming with Spring @EventListener\n- Replace @ApplicationScoped with @Service\n- Remove MicroProfile imports\n\n### RecentQuotePriceChangeList.java:\n- Replace @ApplicationScoped with @Service\n- Replace CDI Event with Spring ApplicationEventPublisher\n- Remove CDI @Inject @QuotePriceChange Event\n\n## 6. EDIT: Interface annotations\n\n### Remove CDI qualifiers from interfaces:\n- RuntimeMode.java: Remove @Qualifier import and annotation, keep as plain annotation\n- TradeEJB.java: Remove @Qualifier, keep as plain annotation  \n- TradeJDBC.java: Remove @Qualifier, keep as plain annotation\n- TradeSession2Direct.java: Remove @Qualifier, keep as plain annotation\n- Trace.java: Remove @InterceptorBinding, keep as plain annotation\n- QuotePriceChange.java: Remove @Qualifier, keep as plain annotation\n- MarketSummaryUpdate.java: Remove @Qualifier, keep as plain annotation\n\n### TradeRunTimeModeLiteral.java:\n- Remove AnnotationLiteral usage (not needed in Spring)\n- Simplify to a plain utility class or remove if not needed\n\n## 7. EDIT: Dockerfile\n\nReplace with:\n```\nFROM maven:3.9.12-ibm-semeru-21-noble\n\nUSER root\nRUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends curl lsof python3-venv python3-full \\\n    && curl -LsSf https://astral.sh/uv/install.sh | sh\n\nENV PATH=\"/root/.local/bin:$PATH\"\nENV PLAYWRIGHT_BROWSERS_PATH=/ms-playwright\nRUN mkdir -p /ms-playwright && chmod 755 /ms-playwright\n\nRUN uv venv /opt/venv \\\n    && uv pip install --python /opt/venv/bin/python playwright==1.47.0 pytest\n\nENV PATH=\"/opt/venv/bin:$PATH\"\nRUN playwright install --with-deps chromium\n\nWORKDIR /app\nCOPY . .\nRUN if [ -f mvnw ]; then chmod +x mvnw; fi && if [ -f smoke.py ]; then chmod +x smoke.py; fi\nRUN mvn clean package -DskipTests\nCMD [\"java\", \"-jar\", \"target/daytrader-spring-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar\"]\n```\n\n## 8. NEW FILE: smoke.py\n\nCreate a smoke test file that tests:\n- GET /rest/trade/market (200)\n- GET /rest/quotes/s:0 (200, returns quote data)\n- POST /rest/trade/login with uid:0/xxx (200)\n- GET /rest/trade/account/uid:0 (200)\n- GET /rest/trade/account/uid:0/holdings (200)\n- POST /rest/trade/buy (200)\n- POST /rest/messaging/ping/broker (200)\n- POST /rest/messaging/ping/streamer (200)\n- GET /rest/messaging/stats (200)\n- GET /rest/app (200, welcome page)\n\nThe smoke.py should accept BASE_URL as environment variable (default http://localhost:8080), use requests library, and print PASS/FAIL for each test.\n\n## 9. DELETE old Quarkus test files\n\nThe Quarkus test files use @QuarkusTest and RestAssured which won't work with Spring Boot. Remove them:\n- src/test/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/TradeResourceTest.java\n- src/test/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/messaging/MessagingTest.java\n- src/test/java/com/ibm/websphere/samples/daytrader/messaging/MessagingResourceTest.java\n\n## IMPORTANT NOTES:\n- Entity classes (AccountDataBean, OrderDataBean, QuoteDataBean, HoldingDataBean, AccountProfileDataBean) should remain UNCHANGED - they use standard JPA annotations that work with both Quarkus and Spring\n- Bean classes (RunStatsDataBean, MarketSummaryDataBean) should remain UNCHANGED\n- Messaging POJOs (OrderMessage, QuoteUpdateMessage) should remain UNCHANGED\n- Utility classes (TradeConfig, Log, MDBStats, TimerStat, FinancialUtils, KeyBlock, KeySequenceDirect) should remain UNCHANGED\n- TradeServices interface should remain UNCHANGED\n- TradeDB interface should remain UNCHANGED\n\nFor the TradeDirect class, the key challenge is UserTransaction. Since TradeDirect manages its own JDBC connections with manual commit/rollback, the simplest approach is:\n- For the 2-phase transaction (ASYNCH_2PHASE mode), simply fall back to using connection-level transactions\n- Remove UserTransaction entirely since TradeDirect already handles connection commits\n- Set inGlobalTxn to false in the places where txn.begin() was called\n- Remove the QuarkusTransaction import\n\nFor the MessageProducerService migration to Spring events:\n- Use ApplicationEventPublisher\n- The DTBroker3MDB and DTStreamer3MDB will use @EventListener to receive events\n\nNow execute ALL these changes. Write every file completely."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01UWVVzdzc77xZKiKvHCX5Ld","session_id":"0a2ab8cf-d9b3-4fb3-875c-ac24a464972f","uuid":"12520a03-41cd-4d54-b548-1dfc3af065f8"}
