{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CvVEqcVvy9gGyXrPUewcjG","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015, 2024.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader;\n    17→\n    18→import org.springframework.boot.SpringApplication;\n    19→import org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.SpringBootApplication;\n    20→import org.springframework.scheduling.annotation.EnableScheduling;\n    21→\n    22→/**\n    23→ * DayTrader Spring Boot Application\n    24→ *\n    25→ * This is the main entry point for the DayTrader application running on Spring Boot 3.x.\n    26→ * It replaces the Quarkus-based configuration.\n    27→ *\n    28→ * @EnableScheduling is required for scheduled tasks like MarketSummarySingleton updates\n    29→ */\n    30→@SpringBootApplication\n    31→@EnableScheduling\n    32→public class DayTraderApplication {\n    33→\n    34→    public static void main(String[] args) {\n    35→        SpringApplication.run(DayTraderApplication.class, args);\n    36→    }\n    37→}\n    38→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0a2ab8cf-d9b3-4fb3-875c-ac24a464972f","uuid":"e6d3114a-5318-420d-8c1d-a27380076765"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01UuibpfVMJgbbP6y8oNzEoz","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→#!/usr/bin/env python3\n     2→\"\"\"\n     3→Smoke tests for DayTrader Spring Boot Application\n     4→Tests the core REST endpoints to verify the application is working correctly.\n     5→\"\"\"\n     6→\n     7→import os\n     8→import sys\n     9→import requests\n    10→\n    11→# Get base URL from environment or use default\n    12→BASE_URL = os.environ.get('BASE_URL', 'http://localhost:8080')\n    13→\n    14→def test_endpoint(method, path, data=None, expected_status=200, test_name=None):\n    15→    \"\"\"Test a single endpoint and return True if successful.\"\"\"\n    16→    url = f\"{BASE_URL}{path}\"\n    17→    test_name = test_name or f\"{method} {path}\"\n    18→\n    19→    try:\n    20→        if method == 'GET':\n    21→            response = requests.get(url, timeout=10)\n    22→        elif method == 'POST':\n    23→            response = requests.post(url, data=data, timeout=10)\n    24→        else:\n    25→            print(f\"FAIL: {test_name} - Unsupported method {method}\")\n    26→            return False\n    27→\n    28→        if response.status_code == expected_status:\n    29→            print(f\"PASS: {test_name} (status={response.status_code})\")\n    30→            return True\n    31→        else:\n    32→            print(f\"FAIL: {test_name} - Expected {expected_status}, got {response.status_code}\")\n    33→            print(f\"      Response: {response.text[:200]}\")\n    34→            return False\n    35→    except requests.exceptions.RequestException as e:\n    36→        print(f\"FAIL: {test_name} - Request error: {str(e)}\")\n    37→        return False\n    38→    except Exception as e:\n    39→        print(f\"FAIL: {test_name} - Unexpected error: {str(e)}\")\n    40→        return False\n    41→\n    42→def run_smoke_tests():\n    43→    \"\"\"Run all smoke tests and return success status.\"\"\"\n    44→    print(f\"Running smoke tests against {BASE_URL}\\n\")\n    45→\n    46→    tests = []\n    47→\n    48→    # Test 1: GET /rest/trade/market - Get market summary\n    49→    tests.append(test_endpoint('GET', '/rest/trade/market',\n    50→                                test_name=\"Get market summary\"))\n    51→\n    52→    # Test 2: GET /rest/quotes/s:0 - Get quote for symbol s:0\n    53→    tests.append(test_endpoint('GET', '/rest/quotes/s:0',\n    54→                                test_name=\"Get quote for s:0\"))\n    55→\n    56→    # Test 3: POST /rest/trade/login - Login user uid:0\n    57→    tests.append(test_endpoint('POST', '/rest/trade/login',\n    58→                                data={'userID': 'uid:0', 'password': 'xxx'},\n    59→                                test_name=\"Login user uid:0\"))\n    60→\n    61→    # Test 4: GET /rest/trade/account/uid:0 - Get account data\n    62→    tests.append(test_endpoint('GET', '/rest/trade/account/uid:0',\n    63→                                test_name=\"Get account data for uid:0\"))\n    64→\n    65→    # Test 5: GET /rest/trade/account/uid:0/holdings - Get holdings\n    66→    tests.append(test_endpoint('GET', '/rest/trade/account/uid:0/holdings',\n    67→                                test_name=\"Get holdings for uid:0\"))\n    68→\n    69→    # Test 6: POST /rest/trade/buy - Buy stock\n    70→    tests.append(test_endpoint('POST', '/rest/trade/buy',\n    71→                                data={'userID': 'uid:0', 'symbol': 's:1', 'quantity': '10'},\n    72→                                test_name=\"Buy 10 shares of s:1\"))\n    73→\n    74→    # Test 7: POST /rest/messaging/ping/broker - Ping broker\n    75→    tests.append(test_endpoint('POST', '/rest/messaging/ping/broker',\n    76→                                data={'message': 'smoke test'},\n    77→                                test_name=\"Ping broker queue\"))\n    78→\n    79→    # Test 8: POST /rest/messaging/ping/streamer - Ping streamer\n    80→    tests.append(test_endpoint('POST', '/rest/messaging/ping/streamer',\n    81→                                data={'message': 'smoke test'},\n    82→                                test_name=\"Ping streamer topic\"))\n    83→\n    84→    # Test 9: GET /rest/messaging/stats - Get messaging stats\n    85→    tests.append(test_endpoint('GET', '/rest/messaging/stats',\n    86→                                test_name=\"Get messaging stats\"))\n    87→\n    88→    # Test 10: GET /rest/app - Get welcome page\n    89→    tests.append(test_endpoint('GET', '/rest/app',\n    90→                                test_name=\"Get welcome page\"))\n    91→\n    92→    # Summary\n    93→    print(f\"\\n{'='*60}\")\n    94→    passed = sum(tests)\n    95→    total = len(tests)\n    96→    print(f\"Results: {passed}/{total} tests passed\")\n    97→    print(f\"{'='*60}\\n\")\n    98→\n    99→    return all(tests)\n   100→\n   101→if __name__ == '__main__':\n   102→    success = run_smoke_tests()\n   103→    sys.exit(0 if success else 1)\n   104→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0a2ab8cf-d9b3-4fb3-875c-ac24a464972f","uuid":"acae30f9-68a0-41fe-9f1e-928c6c38f007"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01JPtFYa6m5QVUSjtMHepeSi","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→FROM maven:3.9.12-ibm-semeru-21-noble\n     2→\n     3→USER root\n     4→RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends curl lsof python3-venv python3-full \\\n     5→    && curl -LsSf https://astral.sh/uv/install.sh | sh\n     6→\n     7→ENV PATH=\"/root/.local/bin:$PATH\"\n     8→ENV PLAYWRIGHT_BROWSERS_PATH=/ms-playwright\n     9→RUN mkdir -p /ms-playwright && chmod 755 /ms-playwright\n    10→\n    11→RUN uv venv /opt/venv \\\n    12→    && uv pip install --python /opt/venv/bin/python playwright==1.47.0 pytest\n    13→\n    14→ENV PATH=\"/opt/venv/bin:$PATH\"\n    15→RUN playwright install --with-deps chromium\n    16→\n    17→WORKDIR /app\n    18→COPY . .\n    19→RUN if [ -f mvnw ]; then chmod +x mvnw; fi && if [ -f smoke.py ]; then chmod +x smoke.py; fi\n    20→RUN mvn clean package -DskipTests\n    21→CMD [\"java\", \"-jar\", \"target/daytrader-spring-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar\"]\n    22→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0a2ab8cf-d9b3-4fb3-875c-ac24a464972f","uuid":"66a02704-5229-4fdd-98af-f51debc357f1"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01VqiZZMrwMwNHV4cYFVvcWr","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Spring Boot Application Configuration for DayTrader\n     2→# This replaces the Quarkus configuration\n     3→\n     4→# Server Configuration\n     5→server.port=8080\n     6→server.servlet.context-path=/\n     7→\n     8→# Database Configuration (H2 in-memory)\n     9→spring.datasource.url=jdbc:h2:mem:tradedb;DB_CLOSE_DELAY=-1\n    10→spring.datasource.driverClassName=org.h2.Driver\n    11→spring.datasource.username=sa\n    12→spring.datasource.password=\n    13→\n    14→# JPA/Hibernate Configuration\n    15→spring.jpa.database-platform=org.hibernate.dialect.H2Dialect\n    16→spring.jpa.hibernate.ddl-auto=create-drop\n    17→spring.jpa.show-sql=false\n    18→spring.jpa.open-in-view=true\n    19→\n    20→# H2 Console (for debugging)\n    21→spring.h2.console.enabled=true\n    22→\n    23→# Trade Application Configuration\n    24→trade.runtime-mode=EJB3\n    25→trade.order-processing-mode=SYNCH\n    26→trade.max-users=50\n    27→trade.max-quotes=100\n    28→trade.db.populate.on.startup=true\n    29→\n    30→# Jackson Configuration\n    31→spring.jackson.serialization.fail-on-empty-beans=false\n    32→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0a2ab8cf-d9b3-4fb3-875c-ac24a464972f","uuid":"503aa724-8257-4653-b6a1-8463e5644202"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01SUnKD3H2Fdmz3xNTaERyip","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2019.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.jaxrs;\n    17→\n    18→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n    19→\n    20→import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\n    21→import org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity;\n    22→import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.GetMapping;\n    23→import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.PathVariable;\n    24→import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.PostMapping;\n    25→import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.RequestMapping;\n    26→import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.RequestParam;\n    27→import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.RestController;\n    28→\n    29→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.beans.MarketSummaryDataBean;\n    30→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountDataBean;\n    31→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountProfileDataBean;\n    32→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.OrderDataBean;\n    33→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeServices;\n    34→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    35→\n    36→/**\n    37→ * Main Trade REST API resource.\n    38→ * Provides REST endpoints for core trading operations.\n    39→ */\n    40→@RestController\n    41→@RequestMapping(\"/rest/trade\")\n    42→public class TradeResource {\n    43→\n    44→    @Autowired\n    45→    TradeServices tradeService;\n    46→\n    47→    @GetMapping(\"/market\")\n    48→    public ResponseEntity<?> getMarketSummary() {\n    49→        try {\n    50→            MarketSummaryDataBean summary = tradeService.getMarketSummary();\n    51→            return ResponseEntity.ok(summary);\n    52→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    53→            return ResponseEntity.internalServerError().body(e.getMessage());\n    54→        }\n    55→    }\n    56→\n    57→    @PostMapping(\"/login\")\n    58→    public ResponseEntity<?> login(@RequestParam(\"userID\") String userID,\n    59→                         @RequestParam(\"password\") String password) {\n    60→        try {\n    61→            AccountDataBean account = tradeService.login(userID, password);\n    62→            return ResponseEntity.ok(account);\n    63→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    64→            return ResponseEntity.status(401).body(e.getMessage());\n    65→        }\n    66→    }\n    67→\n    68→    @PostMapping(\"/logout/{userID}\")\n    69→    public ResponseEntity<?> logout(@PathVariable(\"userID\") String userID) {\n    70→        try {\n    71→            tradeService.logout(userID);\n    72→            return ResponseEntity.ok().build();\n    73→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    74→            return ResponseEntity.internalServerError().body(e.getMessage());\n    75→        }\n    76→    }\n    77→\n    78→    @GetMapping(\"/account/{userID}\")\n    79→    public ResponseEntity<?> getAccount(@PathVariable(\"userID\") String userID) {\n    80→        try {\n    81→            AccountDataBean account = tradeService.getAccountData(userID);\n    82→            if (account == null) {\n    83→                return ResponseEntity.notFound().build();\n    84→            }\n    85→            return ResponseEntity.ok(account);\n    86→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    87→            return ResponseEntity.internalServerError().body(e.getMessage());\n    88→        }\n    89→    }\n    90→\n    91→    @GetMapping(\"/account/{userID}/profile\")\n    92→    public ResponseEntity<?> getAccountProfile(@PathVariable(\"userID\") String userID) {\n    93→        try {\n    94→            AccountProfileDataBean profile = tradeService.getAccountProfileData(userID);\n    95→            if (profile == null) {\n    96→                return ResponseEntity.notFound().build();\n    97→            }\n    98→            return ResponseEntity.ok(profile);\n    99→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   100→            return ResponseEntity.internalServerError().body(e.getMessage());\n   101→        }\n   102→    }\n   103→\n   104→    @GetMapping(\"/account/{userID}/holdings\")\n   105→    public ResponseEntity<?> getHoldings(@PathVariable(\"userID\") String userID) {\n   106→        try {\n   107→            return ResponseEntity.ok(tradeService.getHoldings(userID));\n   108→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   109→            return ResponseEntity.internalServerError().body(e.getMessage());\n   110→        }\n   111→    }\n   112→\n   113→    @GetMapping(\"/account/{userID}/orders\")\n   114→    public ResponseEntity<?> getOrders(@PathVariable(\"userID\") String userID) {\n   115→        try {\n   116→            return ResponseEntity.ok(tradeService.getOrders(userID));\n   117→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   118→            return ResponseEntity.internalServerError().body(e.getMessage());\n   119→        }\n   120→    }\n   121→\n   122→    @PostMapping(\"/buy\")\n   123→    public ResponseEntity<?> buy(@RequestParam(\"userID\") String userID,\n   124→                       @RequestParam(\"symbol\") String symbol,\n   125→                       @RequestParam(\"quantity\") double quantity) {\n   126→        try {\n   127→            OrderDataBean order = tradeService.buy(userID, symbol, quantity,\n   128→                    TradeConfig.getOrderProcessingMode());\n   129→            return ResponseEntity.ok(order);\n   130→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   131→            return ResponseEntity.internalServerError().body(e.getMessage());\n   132→        }\n   133→    }\n   134→\n   135→    @PostMapping(\"/sell\")\n   136→    public ResponseEntity<?> sell(@RequestParam(\"userID\") String userID,\n   137→                        @RequestParam(\"holdingID\") Integer holdingID) {\n   138→        try {\n   139→            OrderDataBean order = tradeService.sell(userID, holdingID,\n   140→                    TradeConfig.getOrderProcessingMode());\n   141→            return ResponseEntity.ok(order);\n   142→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   143→            return ResponseEntity.internalServerError().body(e.getMessage());\n   144→        }\n   145→    }\n   146→\n   147→    @PostMapping(\"/register\")\n   148→    public ResponseEntity<?> register(@RequestParam(\"userID\") String userID,\n   149→                            @RequestParam(\"password\") String password,\n   150→                            @RequestParam(\"fullname\") String fullname,\n   151→                            @RequestParam(\"address\") String address,\n   152→                            @RequestParam(\"email\") String email,\n   153→                            @RequestParam(\"creditcard\") String creditcard,\n   154→                            @RequestParam(\"openBalance\") String openBalance) {\n   155→        try {\n   156→            BigDecimal balance = new BigDecimal(openBalance);\n   157→            AccountDataBean account = tradeService.register(userID, password, fullname,\n   158→                    address, email, creditcard, balance);\n   159→            return ResponseEntity.ok(account);\n   160→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   161→            return ResponseEntity.internalServerError().body(e.getMessage());\n   162→        }\n   163→    }\n   164→}\n   165→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0a2ab8cf-d9b3-4fb3-875c-ac24a464972f","uuid":"91417dca-ea7c-4c0a-9d5a-95527eaf53ec"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Jd9zMtVy6ZSqUTVNdnBBEb","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2019.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.jaxrs;\n    17→\n    18→import java.util.ArrayList;\n    19→import java.util.List;\n    20→\n    21→import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\n    22→import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.GetMapping;\n    23→import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.PathVariable;\n    24→import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.PostMapping;\n    25→import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.RequestMapping;\n    26→import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.RequestParam;\n    27→import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.RestController;\n    28→\n    29→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.QuoteDataBean;\n    30→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeServices;\n    31→\n    32→/**\n    33→ * Quote REST API resource.\n    34→ * Provides REST endpoints for stock quote operations.\n    35→ */\n    36→@RestController\n    37→@RequestMapping(\"/rest/quotes\")\n    38→public class QuoteResource {\n    39→\n    40→    @Autowired\n    41→    TradeServices tradeService;\n    42→\n    43→    @GetMapping(\"/{symbols}\")\n    44→    public List<QuoteDataBean> quotesGet(@PathVariable(\"symbols\") String symbols) {\n    45→        return getQuotes(symbols);\n    46→    }\n    47→\n    48→    @PostMapping\n    49→    public List<QuoteDataBean> quotesPost(@RequestParam(\"symbols\") String symbols) {\n    50→        return getQuotes(symbols);\n    51→    }\n    52→\n    53→    private List<QuoteDataBean> getQuotes(String symbols) {\n    54→        ArrayList<QuoteDataBean> quoteDataBeans = new ArrayList<>();\n    55→\n    56→        try {\n    57→            String[] symbolsSplit = symbols.split(\",\");\n    58→            for (String symbol : symbolsSplit) {\n    59→                QuoteDataBean quoteData = tradeService.getQuote(symbol.trim());\n    60→                if (quoteData != null) {\n    61→                    quoteDataBeans.add(quoteData);\n    62→                }\n    63→            }\n    64→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    65→            e.printStackTrace();\n    66→        }\n    67→\n    68→        return quoteDataBeans;\n    69→    }\n    70→}\n    71→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0a2ab8cf-d9b3-4fb3-875c-ac24a464972f","uuid":"15a595ff-fe2c-48a8-aba3-726798bf9d3c"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_013gUFXXz43xh1APtJJWyFZn","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.jaxrs;\n    17→\n    18→import java.util.HashMap;\n    19→import java.util.Map;\n    20→\n    21→import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\n    22→import org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity;\n    23→import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.GetMapping;\n    24→import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.PostMapping;\n    25→import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.RequestMapping;\n    26→import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.RequestParam;\n    27→import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.RestController;\n    28→\n    29→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.messaging.MessageProducerService;\n    30→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.MDBStats;\n    31→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TimerStat;\n    32→\n    33→/**\n    34→ * REST Resource for testing and monitoring messaging functionality.\n    35→ * Provides REST endpoints for messaging operations.\n    36→ */\n    37→@RestController\n    38→@RequestMapping(\"/rest/messaging\")\n    39→public class MessagingResource {\n    40→\n    41→    @Autowired\n    42→    MessageProducerService messageProducer;\n    43→\n    44→    // Use singleton pattern - original MDBStats is not CDI-managed\n    45→    private final MDBStats mdbStats = MDBStats.getInstance();\n    46→\n    47→    /**\n    48→     * Send a ping message to the trade broker queue.\n    49→     */\n    50→    @PostMapping(\"/ping/broker\")\n    51→    public ResponseEntity<?> pingBroker(@RequestParam(value = \"message\", required = false) String message) {\n    52→        if (message == null || message.isEmpty()) {\n    53→            message = \"Ping from MessagingResource at \" + System.currentTimeMillis();\n    54→        }\n    55→\n    56→        messageProducer.sendBrokerPing(message);\n    57→\n    58→        Map<String, Object> response = new HashMap<>();\n    59→        response.put(\"status\", \"sent\");\n    60→        response.put(\"destination\", \"trade-broker-queue\");\n    61→        response.put(\"message\", message);\n    62→        response.put(\"timestamp\", System.currentTimeMillis());\n    63→\n    64→        return ResponseEntity.ok(response);\n    65→    }\n    66→\n    67→    /**\n    68→     * Send a ping message to the trade streamer topic.\n    69→     */\n    70→    @PostMapping(\"/ping/streamer\")\n    71→    public ResponseEntity<?> pingStreamer(@RequestParam(value = \"message\", required = false) String message) {\n    72→        if (message == null || message.isEmpty()) {\n    73→            message = \"Ping from MessagingResource at \" + System.currentTimeMillis();\n    74→        }\n    75→\n    76→        messageProducer.sendStreamerPing(message);\n    77→\n    78→        Map<String, Object> response = new HashMap<>();\n    79→        response.put(\"status\", \"sent\");\n    80→        response.put(\"destination\", \"trade-streamer-topic\");\n    81→        response.put(\"message\", message);\n    82→        response.put(\"timestamp\", System.currentTimeMillis());\n    83→\n    84→        return ResponseEntity.ok(response);\n    85→    }\n    86→\n    87→    /**\n    88→     * Get messaging statistics.\n    89→     */\n    90→    @GetMapping(\"/stats\")\n    91→    public ResponseEntity<?> getStats() {\n    92→        Map<String, Object> response = new HashMap<>();\n    93→\n    94→        // MDBStats extends HashMap<String, TimerStat> so iterate directly\n    95→        Map<String, Map<String, Object>> formattedStats = new HashMap<>();\n    96→\n    97→        for (Map.Entry<String, TimerStat> entry : mdbStats.entrySet()) {\n    98→            TimerStat stat = entry.getValue();\n    99→            Map<String, Object> statMap = new HashMap<>();\n   100→            statMap.put(\"count\", stat.getCount());\n   101→            statMap.put(\"minSeconds\", stat.getMinSecs());\n   102→            statMap.put(\"maxSeconds\", stat.getMaxSecs());\n   103→            statMap.put(\"avgSeconds\", stat.getAvgSecs());\n   104→            formattedStats.put(entry.getKey(), statMap);\n   105→        }\n   106→\n   107→        response.put(\"statistics\", formattedStats);\n   108→        response.put(\"timestamp\", System.currentTimeMillis());\n   109→\n   110→        return ResponseEntity.ok(response);\n   111→    }\n   112→\n   113→    /**\n   114→     * Reset messaging statistics.\n   115→     */\n   116→    @PostMapping(\"/stats/reset\")\n   117→    public ResponseEntity<?> resetStats() {\n   118→        mdbStats.reset();\n   119→\n   120→        Map<String, Object> response = new HashMap<>();\n   121→        response.put(\"status\", \"reset\");\n   122→        response.put(\"timestamp\", System.currentTimeMillis());\n   123→\n   124→        return ResponseEntity.ok(response);\n   125→    }\n   126→}\n   127→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0a2ab8cf-d9b3-4fb3-875c-ac24a464972f","uuid":"091de02c-92ea-46b5-8cb0-e754768335f7"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01XiRkeBxMkT8ujH8wxaYcSz","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015, 2024.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.web;\n    17→\n    18→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n    19→import java.util.Collection;\n    20→\n    21→import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\n    22→import org.springframework.http.MediaType;\n    23→import org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity;\n    24→import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.GetMapping;\n    25→import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.PostMapping;\n    26→import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.RequestMapping;\n    27→import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.RequestParam;\n    28→import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.RestController;\n    29→\n    30→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountDataBean;\n    31→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountProfileDataBean;\n    32→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.HoldingDataBean;\n    33→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.OrderDataBean;\n    34→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.QuoteDataBean;\n    35→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeServices;\n    36→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    37→\n    38→/**\n    39→ * TradeAppResource provides the web interface to Trade at /app\n    40→ * This replaces TradeAppServlet from Jakarta EE version\n    41→ */\n    42→@RestController\n    43→@RequestMapping(\"/rest/app\")\n    44→public class TradeAppResource {\n    45→\n    46→    @Autowired\n    47→    TradeServices tradeService;\n    48→\n    49→    // Simple session simulation (in production, use proper session management)\n    50→    private static final ThreadLocal<String> currentUser = new ThreadLocal<>();\n    51→\n    52→    @GetMapping(produces = MediaType.TEXT_HTML_VALUE)\n    53→    public ResponseEntity<String> welcome(@RequestParam(value = \"action\", required = false) String action,\n    54→                           @RequestParam(value = \"uid\", required = false) String uid,\n    55→                           @RequestParam(value = \"symbols\", required = false) String symbols) {\n    56→\n    57→        if (action == null || action.isEmpty()) {\n    58→            return ResponseEntity.ok(buildWelcomePage(\"\"));\n    59→        }\n    60→\n    61→        switch (action) {\n    62→            case \"logout\":\n    63→                currentUser.remove();\n    64→                return ResponseEntity.ok(buildWelcomePage(\"You have been logged out.\"));\n    65→            case \"quotes\":\n    66→                return handleQuotes(symbols);\n    67→            case \"home\":\n    68→                if (currentUser.get() != null) {\n    69→                    return handleHome(currentUser.get());\n    70→                }\n    71→                return ResponseEntity.ok(buildWelcomePage(\"Please log in first.\"));\n    72→            case \"portfolio\":\n    73→                if (currentUser.get() != null) {\n    74→                    return handlePortfolio(currentUser.get());\n    75→                }\n    76→                return ResponseEntity.ok(buildWelcomePage(\"Please log in first.\"));\n    77→            case \"account\":\n    78→                if (currentUser.get() != null) {\n    79→                    return handleAccount(currentUser.get());\n    80→                }\n    81→                return ResponseEntity.ok(buildWelcomePage(\"Please log in first.\"));\n    82→            default:\n    83→                return ResponseEntity.ok(buildWelcomePage(\"Unknown action: \" + action));\n    84→        }\n    85→    }\n    86→\n    87→    @PostMapping(produces = MediaType.TEXT_HTML_VALUE)\n    88→    public ResponseEntity<String> handlePost(@RequestParam(value = \"action\", required = false) String action,\n    89→                               @RequestParam(value = \"uid\", required = false) String uid,\n    90→                               @RequestParam(value = \"passwd\", required = false) String passwd,\n    91→                               @RequestParam(value = \"symbol\", required = false) String symbol,\n    92→                               @RequestParam(value = \"quantity\", required = false) String quantity,\n    93→                               @RequestParam(value = \"holdingID\", required = false) String holdingID,\n    94→                               @RequestParam(value = \"symbols\", required = false) String symbols) {\n    95→\n    96→        if (action == null) {\n    97→            return ResponseEntity.ok(buildWelcomePage(\"\"));\n    98→        }\n    99→\n   100→        switch (action) {\n   101→            case \"login\":\n   102→                return handleLogin(uid, passwd);\n   103→            case \"buy\":\n   104→                return handleBuy(currentUser.get(), symbol, quantity);\n   105→            case \"sell\":\n   106→                return handleSell(currentUser.get(), holdingID);\n   107→            case \"quotes\":\n   108→                return handleQuotes(symbols);\n   109→            default:\n   110→                return welcome(action, uid, symbols);\n   111→        }\n   112→    }\n   113→\n   114→    private ResponseEntity<String> handleLogin(String uid, String passwd) {\n   115→        try {\n   116→            AccountDataBean account = tradeService.login(uid, passwd);\n   117→            if (account != null) {\n   118→                currentUser.set(uid);\n   119→                return handleHome(uid);\n   120→            } else {\n   121→                return ResponseEntity.ok(buildWelcomePage(\"Login failed. Invalid username or password.\"));\n   122→            }\n   123→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   124→            Log.error(e, \"Login failed for user: \" + uid);\n   125→            return ResponseEntity.ok(buildWelcomePage(\"Login error: \" + e.getMessage()));\n   126→        }\n   127→    }\n   128→\n   129→    private ResponseEntity<String> handleHome(String userID) {\n   130→        try {\n   131→            AccountDataBean account = tradeService.getAccountData(userID);\n   132→            Collection<HoldingDataBean> holdings = tradeService.getHoldings(userID);\n   133→            \n   134→            StringBuilder html = new StringBuilder();\n   135→            html.append(getHeader(userID));\n   136→            html.append(\"<h2>Welcome, \").append(userID).append(\"!</h2>\");\n   137→            html.append(\"<h3>Account Summary</h3>\");\n   138→            html.append(\"<table border='1' cellpadding='5'>\");\n   139→            html.append(\"<tr><td>Account ID:</td><td>\").append(account.getAccountID()).append(\"</td></tr>\");\n   140→            html.append(\"<tr><td>Balance:</td><td>$\").append(account.getBalance()).append(\"</td></tr>\");\n   141→            html.append(\"<tr><td>Open Balance:</td><td>$\").append(account.getOpenBalance()).append(\"</td></tr>\");\n   142→            html.append(\"<tr><td>Holdings:</td><td>\").append(holdings.size()).append(\"</td></tr>\");\n   143→            html.append(\"</table>\");\n   144→            \n   145→            // Market Summary\n   146→            html.append(\"<h3>Quick Quote</h3>\");\n   147→            html.append(\"<form method='post' action='/rest/app'>\");\n   148→            html.append(\"<input type='hidden' name='action' value='quotes'/>\");\n   149→            html.append(\"Symbols: <input type='text' name='symbols' placeholder='s:0,s:1,s:2'/>\");\n   150→            html.append(\"<input type='submit' value='Get Quotes'/>\");\n   151→            html.append(\"</form>\");\n   152→            \n   153→            html.append(getFooter());\n   154→            return ResponseEntity.ok(html.toString());\n   155→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   156→            Log.error(e, \"Error getting home page for user: \" + userID);\n   157→            return ResponseEntity.ok(buildWelcomePage(\"Error: \" + e.getMessage()));\n   158→        }\n   159→    }\n   160→\n   161→    private ResponseEntity<String> handlePortfolio(String userID) {\n   162→        try {\n   163→            Collection<HoldingDataBean> holdings = tradeService.getHoldings(userID);\n   164→            \n   165→            StringBuilder html = new StringBuilder();\n   166→            html.append(getHeader(userID));\n   167→            html.append(\"<h2>Portfolio for \").append(userID).append(\"</h2>\");\n   168→            html.append(\"<table border='1' cellpadding='5'>\");\n   169→            html.append(\"<tr><th>Holding ID</th><th>Symbol</th><th>Quantity</th><th>Purchase Price</th><th>Purchase Date</th><th>Action</th></tr>\");\n   170→            \n   171→            for (HoldingDataBean holding : holdings) {\n   172→                html.append(\"<tr>\");\n   173→                html.append(\"<td>\").append(holding.getHoldingID()).append(\"</td>\");\n   174→                html.append(\"<td>\").append(holding.getQuoteID()).append(\"</td>\");\n   175→                html.append(\"<td>\").append(holding.getQuantity()).append(\"</td>\");\n   176→                html.append(\"<td>$\").append(holding.getPurchasePrice()).append(\"</td>\");\n   177→                html.append(\"<td>\").append(holding.getPurchaseDate()).append(\"</td>\");\n   178→                html.append(\"<td>\");\n   179→                html.append(\"<form method='post' action='/rest/app' style='display:inline'>\");\n   180→                html.append(\"<input type='hidden' name='action' value='sell'/>\");\n   181→                html.append(\"<input type='hidden' name='holdingID' value='\").append(holding.getHoldingID()).append(\"'/>\");\n   182→                html.append(\"<input type='submit' value='Sell'/>\");\n   183→                html.append(\"</form>\");\n   184→                html.append(\"</td>\");\n   185→                html.append(\"</tr>\");\n   186→            }\n   187→            html.append(\"</table>\");\n   188→            \n   189→            // Buy form\n   190→            html.append(\"<h3>Buy Stock</h3>\");\n   191→            html.append(\"<form method='post' action='/rest/app'>\");\n   192→            html.append(\"<input type='hidden' name='action' value='buy'/>\");\n   193→            html.append(\"Symbol: <input type='text' name='symbol' placeholder='s:0'/> \");\n   194→            html.append(\"Quantity: <input type='text' name='quantity' placeholder='100'/> \");\n   195→            html.append(\"<input type='submit' value='Buy'/>\");\n   196→            html.append(\"</form>\");\n   197→            \n   198→            html.append(getFooter());\n   199→            return ResponseEntity.ok(html.toString());\n   200→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   201→            Log.error(e, \"Error getting portfolio for user: \" + userID);\n   202→            return ResponseEntity.ok(buildWelcomePage(\"Error: \" + e.getMessage()));\n   203→        }\n   204→    }\n   205→\n   206→    private ResponseEntity<String> handleAccount(String userID) {\n   207→        try {\n   208→            AccountDataBean account = tradeService.getAccountData(userID);\n   209→            AccountProfileDataBean profile = tradeService.getAccountProfileData(userID);\n   210→            \n   211→            StringBuilder html = new StringBuilder();\n   212→            html.append(getHeader(userID));\n   213→            html.append(\"<h2>Account Details for \").append(userID).append(\"</h2>\");\n   214→            html.append(\"<table border='1' cellpadding='5'>\");\n   215→            html.append(\"<tr><td>Account ID:</td><td>\").append(account.getAccountID()).append(\"</td></tr>\");\n   216→            html.append(\"<tr><td>Balance:</td><td>$\").append(account.getBalance()).append(\"</td></tr>\");\n   217→            html.append(\"<tr><td>Open Balance:</td><td>$\").append(account.getOpenBalance()).append(\"</td></tr>\");\n   218→            html.append(\"<tr><td>Creation Date:</td><td>\").append(account.getCreationDate()).append(\"</td></tr>\");\n   219→            html.append(\"<tr><td>Last Login:</td><td>\").append(account.getLastLogin()).append(\"</td></tr>\");\n   220→            html.append(\"<tr><td>Login Count:</td><td>\").append(account.getLoginCount()).append(\"</td></tr>\");\n   221→            html.append(\"<tr><td>Full Name:</td><td>\").append(profile.getFullName()).append(\"</td></tr>\");\n   222→            html.append(\"<tr><td>Email:</td><td>\").append(profile.getEmail()).append(\"</td></tr>\");\n   223→            html.append(\"<tr><td>Address:</td><td>\").append(profile.getAddress()).append(\"</td></tr>\");\n   224→            html.append(\"</table>\");\n   225→            html.append(getFooter());\n   226→            return ResponseEntity.ok(html.toString());\n   227→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   228→            Log.error(e, \"Error getting account for user: \" + userID);\n   229→            return ResponseEntity.ok(buildWelcomePage(\"Error: \" + e.getMessage()));\n   230→        }\n   231→    }\n   232→\n   233→    private ResponseEntity<String> handleQuotes(String symbols) {\n   234→        StringBuilder html = new StringBuilder();\n   235→        String user = currentUser.get();\n   236→        html.append(getHeader(user));\n   237→        html.append(\"<h2>Stock Quotes</h2>\");\n   238→        \n   239→        if (symbols == null || symbols.isEmpty()) {\n   240→            symbols = \"s:0,s:1,s:2,s:3,s:4\";\n   241→        }\n   242→        \n   243→        html.append(\"<table border='1' cellpadding='5'>\");\n   244→        html.append(\"<tr><th>Symbol</th><th>Company</th><th>Price</th><th>Change</th><th>Volume</th>\");\n   245→        if (user != null) {\n   246→            html.append(\"<th>Action</th>\");\n   247→        }\n   248→        html.append(\"</tr>\");\n   249→        \n   250→        try {\n   251→            String[] symbolArray = symbols.split(\",\");\n   252→            for (String symbol : symbolArray) {\n   253→                symbol = symbol.trim();\n   254→                QuoteDataBean quote = tradeService.getQuote(symbol);\n   255→                if (quote != null) {\n   256→                    html.append(\"<tr>\");\n   257→                    html.append(\"<td>\").append(quote.getSymbol()).append(\"</td>\");\n   258→                    html.append(\"<td>\").append(quote.getCompanyName()).append(\"</td>\");\n   259→                    html.append(\"<td>$\").append(quote.getPrice()).append(\"</td>\");\n   260→                    html.append(\"<td>\").append(quote.getChange()).append(\"</td>\");\n   261→                    html.append(\"<td>\").append(quote.getVolume()).append(\"</td>\");\n   262→                    if (user != null) {\n   263→                        html.append(\"<td>\");\n   264→                        html.append(\"<form method='post' action='/rest/app' style='display:inline'>\");\n   265→                        html.append(\"<input type='hidden' name='action' value='buy'/>\");\n   266→                        html.append(\"<input type='hidden' name='symbol' value='\").append(symbol).append(\"'/>\");\n   267→                        html.append(\"<input type='text' name='quantity' value='100' size='5'/>\");\n   268→                        html.append(\"<input type='submit' value='Buy'/>\");\n   269→                        html.append(\"</form>\");\n   270→                        html.append(\"</td>\");\n   271→                    }\n   272→                    html.append(\"</tr>\");\n   273→                }\n   274→            }\n   275→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   276→            html.append(\"<tr><td colspan='6'>Error: \").append(e.getMessage()).append(\"</td></tr>\");\n   277→        }\n   278→        html.append(\"</table>\");\n   279→        \n   280→        html.append(\"<h3>Get More Quotes</h3>\");\n   281→        html.append(\"<form method='post' action='/rest/app'>\");\n   282→        html.append(\"<input type='hidden' name='action' value='quotes'/>\");\n   283→        html.append(\"Symbols (comma-separated): <input type='text' name='symbols' value='\").append(symbols).append(\"'/>\");\n   284→        html.append(\"<input type='submit' value='Get Quotes'/>\");\n   285→        html.append(\"</form>\");\n   286→\n   287→        html.append(getFooter());\n   288→        return ResponseEntity.ok(html.toString());\n   289→    }\n   290→\n   291→    private ResponseEntity<String> handleBuy(String userID, String symbol, String quantity) {\n   292→        if (userID == null) {\n   293→            return ResponseEntity.ok(buildWelcomePage(\"Please log in first.\"));\n   294→        }\n   295→        \n   296→        try {\n   297→            double qty = Double.parseDouble(quantity);\n   298→            OrderDataBean order = tradeService.buy(userID, symbol, qty, 0);\n   299→            \n   300→            StringBuilder html = new StringBuilder();\n   301→            html.append(getHeader(userID));\n   302→            html.append(\"<h2>Order Confirmation</h2>\");\n   303→            html.append(\"<p>Buy order placed successfully!</p>\");\n   304→            html.append(\"<table border='1' cellpadding='5'>\");\n   305→            html.append(\"<tr><td>Order ID:</td><td>\").append(order.getOrderID()).append(\"</td></tr>\");\n   306→            html.append(\"<tr><td>Symbol:</td><td>\").append(symbol).append(\"</td></tr>\");\n   307→            html.append(\"<tr><td>Quantity:</td><td>\").append(quantity).append(\"</td></tr>\");\n   308→            html.append(\"<tr><td>Order Type:</td><td>\").append(order.getOrderType()).append(\"</td></tr>\");\n   309→            html.append(\"<tr><td>Order Status:</td><td>\").append(order.getOrderStatus()).append(\"</td></tr>\");\n   310→            html.append(\"<tr><td>Price:</td><td>$\").append(order.getPrice()).append(\"</td></tr>\");\n   311→            html.append(\"</table>\");\n   312→            html.append(\"<p><a href='/rest/app?action=portfolio'>View Portfolio</a></p>\");\n   313→            html.append(getFooter());\n   314→            return ResponseEntity.ok(html.toString());\n   315→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   316→            Log.error(e, \"Error buying stock for user: \" + userID);\n   317→            return ResponseEntity.ok(buildWelcomePage(\"Buy error: \" + e.getMessage()));\n   318→        }\n   319→    }\n   320→\n   321→    private ResponseEntity<String> handleSell(String userID, String holdingID) {\n   322→        if (userID == null) {\n   323→            return ResponseEntity.ok(buildWelcomePage(\"Please log in first.\"));\n   324→        }\n   325→        \n   326→        try {\n   327→            int hid = Integer.parseInt(holdingID);\n   328→            OrderDataBean order = tradeService.sell(userID, hid, 0);\n   329→            \n   330→            StringBuilder html = new StringBuilder();\n   331→            html.append(getHeader(userID));\n   332→            html.append(\"<h2>Order Confirmation</h2>\");\n   333→            html.append(\"<p>Sell order placed successfully!</p>\");\n   334→            html.append(\"<table border='1' cellpadding='5'>\");\n   335→            html.append(\"<tr><td>Order ID:</td><td>\").append(order.getOrderID()).append(\"</td></tr>\");\n   336→            html.append(\"<tr><td>Order Type:</td><td>\").append(order.getOrderType()).append(\"</td></tr>\");\n   337→            html.append(\"<tr><td>Order Status:</td><td>\").append(order.getOrderStatus()).append(\"</td></tr>\");\n   338→            html.append(\"<tr><td>Quantity:</td><td>\").append(order.getQuantity()).append(\"</td></tr>\");\n   339→            html.append(\"<tr><td>Price:</td><td>$\").append(order.getPrice()).append(\"</td></tr>\");\n   340→            html.append(\"</table>\");\n   341→            html.append(\"<p><a href='/rest/app?action=portfolio'>View Portfolio</a></p>\");\n   342→            html.append(getFooter());\n   343→            return ResponseEntity.ok(html.toString());\n   344→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   345→            Log.error(e, \"Error selling stock for user: \" + userID);\n   346→            return ResponseEntity.ok(buildWelcomePage(\"Sell error: \" + e.getMessage()));\n   347→        }\n   348→    }\n   349→\n   350→    private String buildWelcomePage(String message) {\n   351→        StringBuilder html = new StringBuilder();\n   352→        html.append(\"<!DOCTYPE html>\");\n   353→        html.append(\"<html><head><title>DayTrader - Welcome</title>\");\n   354→        html.append(\"<link rel='stylesheet' href='/style.css' type='text/css'/>\");\n   355→        html.append(\"</head><body>\");\n   356→        html.append(\"<h1>DayTrader - Welcome</h1>\");\n   357→        \n   358→        if (message != null && !message.isEmpty()) {\n   359→            html.append(\"<p style='color:red;'><b>\").append(message).append(\"</b></p>\");\n   360→        }\n   361→        \n   362→        html.append(\"<h3>Login</h3>\");\n   363→        html.append(\"<form method='post' action='/rest/app'>\");\n   364→        html.append(\"<input type='hidden' name='action' value='login'/>\");\n   365→        html.append(\"<table>\");\n   366→        html.append(\"<tr><td>Username:</td><td><input type='text' name='uid' value='uid:0'/></td></tr>\");\n   367→        html.append(\"<tr><td>Password:</td><td><input type='password' name='passwd' value='xxx'/></td></tr>\");\n   368→        html.append(\"<tr><td colspan='2'><input type='submit' value='Login'/></td></tr>\");\n   369→        html.append(\"</table>\");\n   370→        html.append(\"</form>\");\n   371→        \n   372→        html.append(\"<h3>View Quotes (No Login Required)</h3>\");\n   373→        html.append(\"<form method='post' action='/rest/app'>\");\n   374→        html.append(\"<input type='hidden' name='action' value='quotes'/>\");\n   375→        html.append(\"Symbols: <input type='text' name='symbols' value='s:0,s:1,s:2'/>\");\n   376→        html.append(\"<input type='submit' value='Get Quotes'/>\");\n   377→        html.append(\"</form>\");\n   378→        \n   379→        html.append(\"</body></html>\");\n   380→        return html.toString();\n   381→    }\n   382→\n   383→    private String getHeader(String userID) {\n   384→        StringBuilder html = new StringBuilder();\n   385→        html.append(\"<!DOCTYPE html>\");\n   386→        html.append(\"<html><head><title>DayTrader</title>\");\n   387→        html.append(\"<link rel='stylesheet' href='/style.css' type='text/css'/>\");\n   388→        html.append(\"</head><body>\");\n   389→        html.append(\"<div style='background:#003366; color:white; padding:10px;'>\");\n   390→        html.append(\"<img src='/images/dayTraderLogo.gif' alt='DayTrader'/>\");\n   391→        if (userID != null) {\n   392→            html.append(\" | Logged in as: <b>\").append(userID).append(\"</b>\");\n   393→            html.append(\" | <a href='/rest/app?action=home' style='color:white;'>Home</a>\");\n   394→            html.append(\" | <a href='/rest/app?action=portfolio' style='color:white;'>Portfolio</a>\");\n   395→            html.append(\" | <a href='/rest/app?action=account' style='color:white;'>Account</a>\");\n   396→            html.append(\" | <a href='/rest/app?action=quotes' style='color:white;'>Quotes</a>\");\n   397→            html.append(\" | <a href='/rest/app?action=logout' style='color:white;'>Logout</a>\");\n   398→        }\n   399→        html.append(\"</div>\");\n   400→        return html.toString();\n   401→    }\n   402→\n   403→    private String getFooter() {\n   404→        return \"<hr/><p><small>DayTrader - Quarkus Edition</small></p></body></html>\";\n   405→    }\n   406→}\n   407→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0a2ab8cf-d9b3-4fb3-875c-ac24a464972f","uuid":"0789cd56-56ad-4f59-8f5d-26ad3e5ab090"}
